commit.message:
Add ppc64le jobs to Travis CI

As with ARM64, Travis CI supports ppc64le ("Power") now.

I've just mimicked the job that ARM64 does, I think that provides
decent coverage without bloating the test matrix too much. (We could
also test pypy on Power, but I don't think it gets us too much extra
value.)
Disable uploading coverage reports to codecov since it is a constant thorn in my side
Fix an issue with asn1crypto_tests when running egg_info from sdist

commit.message: Run GitHub actions on pull requests
Update deps task to filter by python_version and requires_python

Fix parsing of ObjectIdentifier's first octet.

X.660 §7.6 specifies that the first arc of an OID must be 0 to 2 and
the second arc below arcs 0 and 1 must be 0 to 39. Arc 2 is not
restricted in that way.

The algorithm for parsing ObjectIdentifiers did not work for
OID 2.X with X >= 40.

This change also enforces above restrictions when setting an
ObjectIdentifier.
